## Edge cases

- **Simulator vs device numbers** ŌĆö DO NOT mix. Simulator cold-start times are 2-5x
  faster than real-device. Baselines are bucketed by `simulator | device-low | device-mid
  | device-high`.
- **Thermal throttling on real devices** ŌĆö measurements during a throttle event are
  invalid. Read `adb shell dumpsys thermalservice` / iOS thermal API in the trace
  metadata and discard runs flagged `severe` / `critical`.
- **Battery saver mode** ŌĆö silently caps CPU / GPU. Detect via `dumpsys power` and warn.
- **Hermes vs JSC (RN)** ŌĆö Hermes startup is ~30-40% faster on Android, similar on iOS.
  Baseline must match the engine in use; the skill writes engine into the baseline key.
- **Flutter `--release` vs `--profile`** ŌĆö `--profile` includes tracing overhead;
  numbers are ~5-10% worse than `--release`. Document which mode was used; never compare
  across modes.
- **First-launch caches** ŌĆö OS file cache, dex/JIT, image cache. Always pre-warm. Cold-
  start means cold *app*, not cold *device*.
- **Crashes during measurement** ŌĆö discard the run, log the crash, surface as a separate
  finding (a crashing screen is a worse problem than a slow one).
- **Animation A/B differences** ŌĆö if the new release changed the launch animation
  duration, cold-start can change without any real perf delta. Compare TTI as the
  primary metric in that case.
- **A/B feature flags** ŌĆö if the app reads a remote config at startup, vary it
  deterministically per run or pin a single variant for the measurement.

## Dependencies

- **Xcode 15+** with command-line tools: `xcrun xctrace`, `xcodebuild`, `simctl`.
- **Android Studio Hedgehog+** with Macrobenchmark: add `androidx.benchmark:benchmark-
  macro-junit4` to a `:benchmark` module.
- **`adb`** for snapshots + scrolling automation.
- **Flutter SDK** (when stack is Flutter) for `flutter run --profile --trace-startup`
  and DevTools.
- **`/benchmark`** ŌĆö shares the baseline store and the threshold-configuration format.
- **`/mobile-qa`** ŌĆö flows that the perf skill drives during measurement (scroll, login,
  navigate).
- **Optional**: Firebase Performance SDK / Sentry Mobile / `react-native-performance`
  for in-app instrumentation that bridges from synthetic profile runs to real-user
  numbers.

No new gstack libs beyond shared baseline store.

## Stop gates

- After Step 1 (scope + comparison + matrix) ŌĆö lock these before any device boots.
- After Step 4 (aggregate) ŌĆö if more than half the runs are flagged `noisy`, STOP and
  ask the user whether to re-run with more iterations or accept noisy numbers.
- After Step 7 (report) ŌĆö baseline update is gated on explicit user approval; never
  auto-promote.

The AskUserQuestion call is a tool_use, not prose ŌĆö call the tool directly. Loading the
schema via ToolSearch and writing the recommendation as chat prose is the failure mode
these gates exist to prevent.

